    "body": "### Problem\n\nWith last status 3 I have very beautiful separators between windows\n\nI cannot replicate with other values of laststatus as:\n> Note that \"horiz\", \"horizup\", \"horizdown\", \"vertleft\", \"vertright\" and\n\t\"verthoriz\" are only used when 'laststatus' is 3, since only vertical\n\twindow separators are used otherwise.\n\nI love clean UIs and as such have a strong dislike for statusline (I already made so the tabline show the name of the window's buffer)\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nA way to define beautiful separators (laststatus 3) + no status line (laststatus 0)\nIt could be last status 4, even though I do not find having numbers very clear and force for every combinations of option (e.g.: 3 + 0) to have a new number",
